<?xml version="1.0"?>
<block>
  <name>Calculator</name>
  <key>Calculation_Calculator</key>
  <category>Calculation</category>
  <import>import gnuradio.calculation.Calculator</import>
  <make>gnuradio.calculation.Calculator.Calculator($num_inputs,$in_var)
self.$(id).set_parameters($Exp,$num_inputs)</make>


<param>
<name>Input Variables</name>
<key>in_var</key>
<value>"[]"</value>
<type>string</type>
</param>


<param>
<name>Expression</name>
<key>Exp</key>
<type>string</type>
</param>


<param>
<name>Num inputs</name>
<key>num_inputs</key>
<value>1</value>
<type>int</type>
</param>

  <sink>
    <name>in0</name>
    <type>float</type>
    <nports>$num_inputs</nports>
  </sink>
<!--
  <sink>
  <name>in1</name>
  <type>float</type>
  <nports>4</nports>
  </sink> -->

  
  <source>
    <name>out</name>
    <type>float</type>
  </source>

<doc>

Variable names must be a0,a1,a2 and so on.

You can use maximum 10 variables per block.

Example to add 5 variables:

"a0+a1+a2+a3+a4"

To perform Exponential(power) calculations on operators use the following:

a0**a1 

To perform calculations like sqrt, log or exp use the following:

sqrt(a4)

log(a2)

exp(a8)

</doc>

</block>
